Quote: Jonah Lomu is such a darling of the British tabloids that he is within cooee of turning into a verb. Harry Orsman reports that a mystery yarn by Hilary Bonner, A Fancy to Kill For, includes the immortal line, "He came at her like Jonah Lomu. His bulk catapulted itself through the doorway... If this catches on, it won't be long before Jonah's name will become lower case. We'll have the hero poised to lomu through the door and everyone will.know instantly what the author means.
